abstract.text: Creates an XML representation of a MIDISetup object.

inlineContent.text: The MIDISetup object whose XML representation is to be returned.
On successful return, points to a newly-created CFDataRef containing the XML text. The client is responsible for releasing this CFData object when done with it.
As of CoreMIDI 1.1, it is usually not necessary to call this function, as CoreMIDI manages a single persistent MIDISetup itself.

abstract.text: Communicate with MIDI devices such as hardware keyboards and synthesizers.
A type that represents the global state of the MIDI system, that contains lists of the devices and serial port owners.
Creates an XML representation of a MIDISetup object.
A reference to an immutable CFData object.
